
[1]amortizement

   AMORTIZA'TION or AMORT'IZEMENT, n. The act or right of alienating lands
   or tenements to a corporation, which was considered formerly as
   transferring them to dead hands, as such alienations were mostly made
   to religious houses for superstitious uses.
